# Cursor Rules for SVG Mockup Generation and UI/UX Design

## SVG File Creation Rules

### XML/SVG Encoding and Comments
- **ALWAYS** use only ASCII characters (0x00-0x7F) in XML comments
- **NEVER** use non-ASCII characters (Cyrillic, special symbols, emoji) in XML comments
- Use English language for all XML/SVG comments
- Format: `<!-- English comment text -->`
- Validate XML syntax before saving files

### SVG Structure Best Practices
- Include proper XML declaration: `<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>`
- Define reusable elements in `<defs>` section (gradients, filters, patterns)
- Use semantic IDs for all major elements (e.g., `id="leftSidebar"`, `id="topHeader"`)
- Group related elements using `<g>` tags with descriptive IDs
- Add layout guides for Figma with low opacity (opacity="0.1") for alignment

### Color and Styling
- Use hex color codes for consistency (#RRGGBB format)
- Define color palettes in README documentation
- Use gradients for backgrounds when appropriate
- Apply shadows/filters through SVG `<filter>` definitions

### File Organization
- Create corresponding README.md file for each mockup
- Include:
  - Description of the mockup
  - File structure
  - Usage instructions for Figma
  - Color palette
  - Dimensions and spacing
  - Typography guidelines
  - Component breakdown

## Error Prevention

### Before Saving SVG Files
1. Check all comments contain only ASCII characters
2. Validate XML syntax
3. Ensure all opening tags have closing tags
4. Verify all attribute values are properly quoted
5. Test file opens correctly in browser

### Common Issues to Avoid
- ❌ Non-ASCII characters in comments (causes XML parsing errors)
- ❌ Unclosed tags
- ❌ Unquoted attribute values
- ❌ Invalid XML entities
- ❌ Missing namespace declarations

