## Fixing Encoding Issues

### If XML Parsing Errors Occur
1. **Check for non-ASCII characters**: Use grep or search to find problematic comments
2. **Replace all non-ASCII comments**: Convert to English ASCII-only comments
3. **Validate XML**: Use XML parser or browser to test
4. **PowerShell command for bulk fix** (if needed):

```powershell
$content = [System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('file.svg', [System.Text.Encoding]::UTF8)
$lines = $content -split "`r?`n"
for ($i = 0; $i -lt $lines.Length; $i++) {
    if ($lines[$i] -match '<!--.*[^\x20-\x7E\x09].*-->') {
        $lines[$i] = $lines[$i] -replace '<!--.*[^\x20-\x7E\x09].*-->', '<!-- English comment -->'
    }
}
[System.IO.File]::WriteAllText('mockup_file.svg', ($lines -join "`r`n"), [System.Text.Encoding]::UTF8)
```